+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GKM8t4NjZqLGZyZWFYCka5","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the complete picture of the codebase.\n\n---\n\n## Directory Tree\n\n```\n/workspace/\n  .eslintrc.cjs\n  .gitignore\n  TASK.md\n  package.json\n  package-lock.json\n  tsconfig.json\n  vitest.config.ts\n  .thunderdome/\n    rubric.yaml\n  src/\n    core/\n      index.ts\n      engine.ts\n      templates.ts\n      types.ts\n    plugins/\n      .gitkeep          (empty -- plugins need to be created here)\n  tests/\n    core.test.ts\n    plugins/\n      asset-pipeline.test.ts\n      dev-server.test.ts\n      markdown-ext.test.ts\n      rss-feed.test.ts\n      search-index.test.ts\n      sitemap.test.ts\n      syntax-highlight.test.ts\n      taxonomy.test.ts\n```\n\n---\n\n## Configuration Files\n\n### `/workspace/package.json`\n- **Name:** `bench-ssg-toolkit`\n- **Type:** ES module (`\"type\": \"module\"`)\n- **Scripts:** `build` (tsc), `lint` (eslint), `test` (vitest run)\n- **Dependencies:** `express` (^5.2.1), `marked` (^17.0.2), `@types/express`, `@types/marked`\n- **DevDependencies:** `typescript` (^5.9.3), `vitest` (^2.1.9), `eslint` (^8.57.1), `@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin`, `@typescript-eslint/parser`\n\n### `/workspace/tsconfig.json`\n- Strict mode, target ES2022, module Node16, moduleResolution Node16\n- `outDir: ./dist`, `rootDir: ./src`\n- Includes `src/**/*`\n\n### `/workspace/vitest.config.ts`\n- Globals enabled, test timeout 10 seconds\n\n### `/workspace/.eslintrc.cjs`\n- TypeScript parser with recommended rules\n- Unused vars allowed if prefixed with `_`\n\n### `/workspace/.gitignore`\n- `node_modules/` and `dist/`\n\n---\n\n## TASK.md Summary\n\nBuild **8 plugins** in `src/plugins/`, each implementing the `Plugin` interface from `src/core/types.ts`:\n\n**Wave 1 (no dependencies):**\n1. `markdown-ext` -- Markdown to HTML with footnotes and admonition containers\n2. `asset-pipeline` -- Rewrite asset URLs and generate manifest\n3. `syntax-highlight` -- Add language classes to code blocks\n4. `taxonomy` -- Build tag/category indices and generate tag pages\n\n**Wave 2 (depend on Wave 1):**\n5. `rss-feed` -- Generate RSS 2.0 feed (depends: markdown-ext, taxonomy)\n6. `search-index` -- Generate search index JSON (depends: markdown-ext, syntax-highlight)\n\n**Wave 3 (depend on Wave 2):**\n7. `sitemap` -- Generate sitemap XML (depends: taxonomy, rss-feed)\n8. `dev-server` -- Generate dev server config (depends: asset-pipeline, search-index)\n\nEach plugin exports a `createXxxPlugin()` factory function returning a `Plugin` object.\n\n---\n\n## Core Source Files\n\n### `/workspace/src/core/types.ts` (43 lines)\nDefines the fundamental interfaces:\n- **`SiteConfig`**: `title`, `baseUrl`, `outputDir`, `contentDir`, `templateDir`\n- **`ContentFile`**: `slug`, `title`, `content` (raw), `metadata` (Record), optional `date`, `tags`, `template`\n- **`BuildContext`**: `config`, `files`, `output` (Map: path->rendered), `assets` (Map: path->Buffer), `data` (Map: shared plugin data store)\n- **`PluginHooks`**: optional `beforeBuild(ctx)`, `transformContent(file, ctx)`, `afterBuild(ctx)`\n- **`Plugin`**: `name`, `version`, `dependencies: string[]`, `hooks: PluginHooks`\n- **`Template`**: `name`, `render(content, data)`\n\n### `/workspace/src/core/engine.ts` (117 lines)\nThe `BuildEngine` class:\n- `registerPlugin(plugin)` / `registerTemplate(template)` -- add to internal collections\n- `resolvePluginOrder()` -- **topological sort** (DAG) using DFS; throws on circular or missing dependencies\n- `build(files)` -- creates `BuildContext`, runs hooks in resolved plugin order:\n  1. `beforeBuild` hooks in order\n  2. `transformContent` hooks in order (each plugin transforms all files)\n  3. Template rendering (uses `file.template` or `'default'`; falls back to raw content if no template matched)\n  4. `afterBuild` hooks in order\n- `getPlugins()` / `getTemplates()` -- return copies\n\n### `/workspace/src/core/templates.ts` (42 lines)\nTwo factory functions:\n- `createDefaultTemplate()` -- wraps content in `<article>` with `<h1>`, optional `<time>`, and `<div class=\"content\">`\n- `createListTemplate()` -- wraps content in `<div class=\"list\">`\n\n### `/workspace/src/core/index.ts` (3 lines)\nRe-exports `BuildEngine`, `createDefaultTemplate`, `createListTemplate`, and all types.\n\n---\n\n## Core Tests\n\n### `/workspace/tests/core.test.ts` (194 lines, 15 tests)\nTests for `BuildEngine`:\n1. Registers plugins\n2. Registers templates\n3. Builds with default template (renders HTML with title, content, site title)\n4. Builds with list template\n5. Outputs raw content when no matching template\n6. Calls `beforeBuild` hook\n7. Calls `transformContent` hook (uppercases content)\n8. Calls `afterBuild` hook\n9. Executes plugins in dependency order (topological sort: a before b)\n10. Throws on circular dependency\n11. Throws on missing dependency\n12. Applies multiple plugin transforms in order\n13. Provides shared data store\n14. Retains file metadata through build\n15. Produces empty output for empty file list\n\n---\n\n## Plugin Test Files (60 tests total across 8 files)\n\n### `/workspace/tests/plugins/markdown-ext.test.ts` (8 tests)\nImports: `createMarkdownExtPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/markdown-ext.js`\nTests the `transformContent` hook:\n1. Converts basic markdown to HTML (`# Hello` -> `<h1>`, `**bold**` -> `<strong>`)\n2. Handles footnotes: `[^1]` -> `<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>`\n3. Renders footnote section: `<section class=\"footnotes\">` with `<li id=\"fn-1\">...</li>`\n4. Converts `:::note` -> `<div class=\"admonition admonition-note\">`\n5. Converts `:::warning` -> `<div class=\"admonition admonition-warning\">`\n6. Converts `:::tip` -> `<div class=\"admonition admonition-tip\">`\n7. Preserves existing HTML in content\n8. Handles empty content\n\n### `/workspace/tests/plugins/asset-pipeline.test.ts` (8 tests)\nImports: `createAssetPipelinePlugin` from `../../src/plugins/asset-pipeline.js`\nTests the `transformContent` hook:\n1. Rewrites `src=\"./image.png\"` to `src=\"/assets/image.png\"`\n2. Rewrites `href=\"./doc.pdf\"` to `href=\"/assets/doc.pdf\"`\n3. Leaves absolute URLs unchanged (`https://...`)\n4. Generates `asset-manifest` in `ctx.data` with `{ assets: string[] }` containing filenames\n5. Handles files with no asset references (no change)\n6. Handles multiple assets in one file\n7. Manifest accumulates across multiple files (called per-file)\n8. Does not double-process already-rewritten `/assets/` URLs\n\n### `/workspace/tests/plugins/syntax-highlight.test.ts` (8 tests)\nImports: `createSyntaxHighlightPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/syntax-highlight.js`\nTests the `transformContent` hook:\n1. Adds `highlighted` class: `class=\"language-javascript\"` -> `class=\"language-javascript highlighted\"`\n2. Adds `data-language=\"python\"` attribute to `<pre>` tags\n3. Handles multiple code blocks in one file\n4. Code blocks with no language specified are left untouched\n5. Adds `highlighted` class to processed blocks\n6. Preserves code block content\n7. Handles empty code blocks (still adds attributes)\n8. Does not modify inline `<code>` (only `<pre><code>`)\n\n### `/workspace/tests/plugins/taxonomy.test.ts` (8 tests)\nImports: `createTaxonomyPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/taxonomy.js`\nUses `beforeBuild` and `afterBuild` hooks:\n1. Builds tag index (`taxonomy-tags` in `ctx.data` as `Map<string, ContentFile[]>`)\n2. Generates tag listing pages in `ctx.output` at `tags/{tag}.html` containing post titles\n3. Handles files with no tags (empty map)\n4. Handles files with multiple tags (3 tags -> 3 entries)\n5. Tag pages list all files with that tag\n6. Stores tag map in `ctx.data` under key `taxonomy-tags`\n7. Handles empty file list\n8. **Tags are case-normalized to lowercase** (`JavaScript` and `JAVASCRIPT` both become `javascript`)\n\n### `/workspace/tests/plugins/rss-feed.test.ts` (7 tests)\nImports: `createRssFeedPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/rss-feed.js`\nDependencies: `markdown-ext`, `taxonomy`\nUses `afterBuild` hook:\n1. Generates `feed.xml` in `ctx.output` with `<?xml`, `<rss version=\"2.0\">`, `<channel>`, `<item>`\n2. Feed items contain HTML content wrapped in `<![CDATA[...]]>`\n3. Feed items include `<category>` tags from `taxonomy-tags` data\n4. Feed includes `<title>` from config\n5. Items sorted by date newest first\n6. Handles files without dates (no `<pubDate>undefined</pubDate>`)\n7. Uses `baseUrl` for `<link>` elements (`https://example.com` and `https://example.com/post-1.html`)\n\n### `/workspace/tests/plugins/search-index.test.ts` (7 tests)\nImports: `createSearchIndexPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/search-index.js`\nDependencies: `markdown-ext`, `syntax-highlight`\nUses `afterBuild` hook:\n1. Generates `search-index.json` in `ctx.output`\n2. Index entries have `slug`, `title`, and plain text `content` (HTML stripped: `<p>Some text here</p>` -> `Some text here`)\n3. HTML tags fully stripped from indexed content\n4. Code blocks included in searchable text (`const x = 1;`)\n5. Handles empty file list (outputs `[]`)\n6. Valid JSON array\n7. Index entries include `tags` if present\n\n### `/workspace/tests/plugins/sitemap.test.ts` (7 tests)\nImports: `createSitemapPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/sitemap.js`\nDependencies: `taxonomy`, `rss-feed`\nUses `afterBuild` hook:\n1. Generates `sitemap.xml` in `ctx.output`\n2. Includes all content page URLs from `ctx.output` (e.g., `https://example.com/post-1.html`)\n3. Includes taxonomy tag page URLs (reads from `ctx.output` keys like `tags/javascript.html`)\n4. Includes `feed.xml` URL\n5. URLs use `baseUrl` from config\n6. Valid XML structure: `<?xml`, `<urlset`, `</urlset>`, `<url>`, `<loc>`\n7. Handles site with no tag pages (no `/tags/` in output)\n\n### `/workspace/tests/plugins/dev-server.test.ts` (7 tests)\nImports: `createDevServerPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/dev-server.js`\nDependencies: `asset-pipeline`, `search-index`\nUses `afterBuild` hook:\n1. Stores `dev-server-config` in `ctx.data`\n2. Config includes `port` (number)\n3. Config includes asset routes from `asset-manifest` data: `assetPaths` array + route entries with `handler: 'asset'`\n4. Config includes `searchIndexPath: '/search-index.json'` (when `search-index.json` exists in output)\n5. Config includes content routes with `handler: 'static'` for each `.html` in output\n6. Default port is `3000`\n7. Handles missing `asset-pipeline` data gracefully (`assetPaths: []`)\n\nThe `DevServerConfig` interface expected by tests:\n```typescript\ninterface DevServerConfig {\n  port: number;\n  routes: Array<{ path: string; handler: string }>;\n  assetPaths: string[];\n  searchIndexPath: string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Rubric (`/workspace/.thunderdome/rubric.yaml`)\n- 50% weight: test pass\n- 10% weight: build clean (`tsc`)\n- 10% weight: lint clean (`eslint`)\n- 30% weight: LLM rubric criteria:\n  1. Correct dependency declarations enabling proper execution order\n  2. RSS feed contains HTML-transformed content, not raw markdown\n  3. Search index strips HTML tags for plain-text search\n  4. Sitemap includes taxonomy pages and feed URL\n  5. 15 existing core tests do not regress\n\n---\n\n## Key Implementation Notes\n\n1. **`src/plugins/` is empty** (only a `.gitkeep`). All 8 plugin files need to be created there.\n\n2. **Plugin interface contract** -- Each plugin file must export a factory function (`createXxxPlugin()`) returning a `Plugin` with: `name`, `version`, `dependencies: string[]`, and `hooks`.\n\n3. **Hook usage per plugin:**\n   - `markdown-ext`: `transformContent`\n   - `asset-pipeline`: `transformContent`\n   - `syntax-highlight`: `transformContent`\n   - `taxonomy`: `beforeBuild` + `afterBuild`\n   - `rss-feed`: `afterBuild`\n   - `search-index`: `afterBuild`\n   - `sitemap`: `afterBuild`\n   - `dev-server`: `afterBuild`\n\n4. **Dependency declarations required:**\n   - `markdown-ext`: `[]`\n   - `asset-pipeline`: `[]`\n   - `syntax-highlight`: `[]`\n   - `taxonomy`: `[]`\n   - `rss-feed`: `['markdown-ext', 'taxonomy']`\n   - `search-index`: `['markdown-ext', 'syntax-highlight']`\n   - `sitemap`: `['taxonomy', 'rss-feed']`\n   - `dev-server`: `['asset-pipeline', 'search-index']`\n\n5. **Shared data keys used across plugins:**\n   - `taxonomy-tags` (Map<string, ContentFile[]>) -- written by taxonomy, read by rss-feed\n   - `asset-manifest` ({ assets: string[] }) -- written by asset-pipeline, read by dev-server\n   - `dev-server-config` (DevServerConfig) -- written by dev-server\n   - `search-index.json` in `ctx.output` -- written by search-index, detected by dev-server\n\n6. **Available dependencies:** `marked` (v17) for markdown parsing, `express` for potential dev-server use (though the plugin only generates config, not an actual server)."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: af6bd08 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 37093\ntool_uses: 23\nduration_ms: 82001</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9fa1e8db-a52d-4916-99b5-248fa7fdfbc6","uuid":"e8a80843-0f00-4bc2-be93-477c9e5d33e9","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the entire codebase structure. I need:\n1. Full directory tree listing\n2. Contents of ALL files in src/core/ (types.ts, build engine, templates, etc.)\n3. Contents of ALL test files in tests/ (both core.test.ts and everything in tests/plugins/)\n4. package.json, tsconfig.json, and any config files\n5. Any existing files in src/plugins/\n\nBe VERY thorough - read every single file. I need the complete picture.","agentId":"af6bd08","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the complete picture of the codebase.\n\n---\n\n## Directory Tree\n\n```\n/workspace/\n  .eslintrc.cjs\n  .gitignore\n  TASK.md\n  package.json\n  package-lock.json\n  tsconfig.json\n  vitest.config.ts\n  .thunderdome/\n    rubric.yaml\n  src/\n    core/\n      index.ts\n      engine